    "updated_at": "2014-10-23T19:52:12Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We discussed this in the dev meeting today, and decided that language info makes more sense in a kernel info reply than in static kernelspecs. Min highlighted the potential problems if people are making one kernelspec for every environment: the more information there is in kernelspecs, the more likely it is that they get out of date, and that's problematic if you have a lot of them. Information that's in a kernel info reply will always be up to date with the relevant kernel code.\n"
  },
